1
00:00:54,640 --> 00:00:55,159
You...

2
00:00:56,280 --> 00:00:56,840
You're practicing?

3
00:00:58,439 --> 00:00:59,320
I forgot

4
00:00:59,840 --> 00:01:00,799
to take my speaker back.

5
00:01:01,840 --> 00:01:02,840
I need to take it back.

6
00:01:03,640 --> 00:01:04,480
Okay, sorry.

7
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,120
What brings you here?

8
00:02:05,359 --> 00:02:06,840
He wants to learn dancing from you.

9
00:02:13,159 --> 00:02:15,159
I'm not very good at dancing.

10
00:02:15,479 --> 00:02:16,919
Forget it.

11
00:02:24,159 --> 00:02:24,879
I want to learn.

12
00:02:33,599 --> 00:02:34,120
Okay.

13
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:38,280
Come on.

14
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:41,199
Put your left hand on my shoulder.

15
00:02:43,599 --> 00:02:45,199
Let's hold hands with our right hands.

16
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:46,879
Then,

17
00:02:47,719 --> 00:02:49,039
step your right foot forward.

18
00:02:49,919 --> 00:02:50,719
I'll step back with my left foot.

19
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:52,240
Left leg.

20
00:02:52,639 --> 00:02:53,960
Right, right, one, two.

21
00:02:55,319 --> 00:02:56,120
Are you okay, Dad?

22
00:02:56,919 --> 00:02:57,400
You...

23
00:02:57,840 --> 00:02:59,840
You're really clumsier than me.

24
00:03:00,479 --> 00:03:01,199
Did you forget

25
00:03:01,479 --> 00:03:02,680
when I learned to ride a bike,

26
00:03:02,719 --> 00:03:03,800
you taught me for two weeks.

27
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:07,159
Yeah,

28
00:03:07,439 --> 00:03:08,479
how could I forget that?

29
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:10,199
When you were little,

30
00:03:11,159 --> 00:03:12,960
you were the slowest to walk.

31
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:16,159
Don't be afraid of being slow.

32
00:03:16,719 --> 00:03:17,240
Keep practicing.

33
00:03:19,159 --> 00:03:19,599
Come on.

34
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:24,520
[It's really good.]

35
00:03:25,639 --> 00:03:26,479
[In my memory,]

36
00:03:27,159 --> 00:03:28,520
[touching my father's hand]

37
00:03:29,599 --> 00:03:31,240
was many years ago.

38
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:33,280
When I was a child,

39
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:35,639
my father's palm was so big.

40
00:03:35,639 --> 00:03:36,159
Come on.

41
00:03:36,919 --> 00:03:38,120
Even if I fell,

42
00:03:39,039 --> 00:03:41,039
he could hold my world.

43
00:03:43,919 --> 00:03:45,439
He was always in a hurry at work,

44
00:03:46,199 --> 00:03:47,759
and his temper was more unpredictable than the weather.

45
00:03:49,919 --> 00:03:51,319
But when he drew the drawings,

46
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:54,280
his hand was so steady.

47
00:03:58,840 --> 00:03:59,960
My father never wrote

48
00:04:00,879 --> 00:04:02,520
any love letters in his life,

49
00:04:03,919 --> 00:04:04,960
[but he paid countless respects]

50
00:04:05,719 --> 00:04:06,919
[to the sky.]

51
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:09,680
[That's his romance.]

52
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:12,360
[Many years later,]

53
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:14,520
[I finally understood]

54
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:16,639
[his unsaid feelings.]

55
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:20,680
[I also paid respects to the sky]

56
00:04:21,680 --> 00:04:22,360
[like him.]

57
00:04:23,759 --> 00:04:24,720
What is he doing?

58
00:04:24,839 --> 00:04:25,839
Yeah, why is he saluting?

59
00:04:25,920 --> 00:04:26,839
He's even crying.

60
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:57,120
It's so hard.

61
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:01,000
Look at you, so clumsy.

62
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:04,360
Honey,

63
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:05,800
you look stunning.

64
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:06,959
In that wedding dress,

65
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:08,720
you look like you've stepped out of a painting.

66
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:09,759
You're so beautiful.

67
00:06:10,040 --> 00:06:10,759
What I'm wearing

68
00:06:10,879 --> 00:06:12,279
doesn't make me look like a painting?

69
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:18,519
The kids are here.

70
00:06:21,959 --> 00:06:23,040
Sir, please have some water.

71
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:24,000
Let me take a good look at you.

72
00:06:26,959 --> 00:06:28,319
Miss Lan, your dress looks perfect.

73
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:36,680
Xiaochuan, come out.

74
00:07:03,399 --> 00:07:03,879
It looks great.

75
00:07:03,879 --> 00:07:04,720
Miss Lan,

76
00:07:04,839 --> 00:07:06,160
you look great in anything.

77
00:07:06,279 --> 00:07:07,480
This time you're trying on a dress,

78
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:08,800
next time, a wedding dress.

79
00:07:09,519 --> 00:07:11,160
When are you getting married?

80
00:07:12,079 --> 00:07:12,959
No, no, no.

81
00:07:13,399 --> 00:07:14,199
He's my brother.

82
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:15,560
We're relatives.

83
00:07:17,319 --> 00:07:18,120
Yeah.

84
00:07:18,319 --> 00:07:19,759
This is my daughter,

85
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:20,839
and that's my son.

86
00:07:20,959 --> 00:07:21,920
A pair of siblings.

87
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:23,279
Excuse me.

88
00:07:23,439 --> 00:07:24,399
It's so pretty.

89
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:25,639
This color

90
00:07:25,759 --> 00:07:27,839
really brings out your skin tone.

91
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:28,759
Really?

92
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:30,000
If you think this one's good,

93
00:07:30,199 --> 00:07:31,040
I'll go with it.

94
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,279
When I get married,

95
00:07:33,519 --> 00:07:34,639
I'll have you pick out my dress too.

96
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:35,560
Sure.

97
00:07:37,279 --> 00:07:37,920
Sweetie,

98
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:39,480
when do you plan to get married?

99
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:42,120
Get married?

100
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:44,519
I'm waiting for my brother

101
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:46,079
to introduce me to a good match.

102
00:07:47,319 --> 00:07:48,199
It's beautiful.

103
00:07:50,360 --> 00:07:50,920
Auntie,

104
00:07:51,759 --> 00:07:52,480
I'll go with this one.

105
00:07:52,759 --> 00:07:54,439
Today is your wedding dress fitting.

106
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:56,040
Try on more and choose carefully.

107
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:56,639
Okay.

108
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:57,279
Go ahead.

109
00:07:58,040 --> 00:07:58,519
Dad.

110
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:11,399
Hello.

111
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:13,879
Please come in and help me with the back strap.

112
00:08:29,199 --> 00:08:29,680
Don't move.

113
00:08:31,319 --> 00:08:32,440
If you tear it, you'll have to pay.

114
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:35,480
Who let you in?

115
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:39,360
You did.

116
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,559
I thought you were the salesperson.

117
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:43,480
I have something to tell you.

118
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:45,799
My dad asked me to thank you.

119
00:08:46,639 --> 00:08:47,879
But please don't tell your dad

120
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:50,720
that he went to the square to reminisce again yesterday.

121
00:08:52,879 --> 00:08:53,559
Don't worry.

122
00:08:54,279 --> 00:08:55,399
I'll definitely

123
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,399
save your dad's face.

124
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,320
I have something to say too.

125
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:06,720
Now that my mom has made up with my dad,

126
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:08,519
from now on,

127
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:09,919
we'll just continue

128
00:09:11,039 --> 00:09:12,000
being brother and sister.

129
00:09:12,559 --> 00:09:13,120
Brother and sister?

130
00:09:13,879 --> 00:09:14,440
Got it?

131
00:09:16,559 --> 00:09:17,720
Can you avoid me?

132
00:09:18,879 --> 00:09:19,679
I'll try my best to avoid you.

133
00:09:21,799 --> 00:09:23,120
Anyway, we'll see less of each other.

134
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:24,840
It would be best if the next time we meet

135
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:26,200
is at my wedding.

136
00:09:30,639 --> 00:09:31,559
How do you know?

137
00:09:34,759 --> 00:09:36,000
Aren't you marrying me?

138
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:41,799
You can handle the rest.

139
00:10:05,039 --> 00:10:06,159
Hello, Mr. Jin.

140
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:07,080
Hello.

141
00:10:10,519 --> 00:10:11,240
Mr. Jin,

142
00:10:11,399 --> 00:10:12,639
this is our design for this season.

143
00:10:12,840 --> 00:10:13,799
We would appreciate your guidance.

144
00:10:17,120 --> 00:10:17,639
Not good.

145
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:18,720
Not good.

146
00:10:19,519 --> 00:10:20,000
Not good.

147
00:10:20,679 --> 00:10:21,159
Not good.

148
00:10:21,759 --> 00:10:22,200
Not good.

149
00:10:24,440 --> 00:10:25,200
That's all.

150
00:10:25,679 --> 00:10:26,399
There's one more.

151
00:10:26,559 --> 00:10:27,480
The customer inside is trying it on.

152
00:10:40,879 --> 00:10:41,519
Auntie.

153
00:10:47,159 --> 00:10:47,879
Caien.

154
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,080
Oh my goodness.

155
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:49,960
Auntie.

156
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:53,080
How many years have we not seen each other?

157
00:10:53,159 --> 00:10:54,039
Yeah.

158
00:10:54,159 --> 00:10:55,080
What are you doing?

159
00:10:55,639 --> 00:10:56,480
Are you getting married?

160
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:00,679
We haven't seen each other for so many years.

161
00:11:00,879 --> 00:11:02,759
You look like a painting.

162
00:11:02,919 --> 00:11:03,639
So pretty.

163
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:05,279
You were just a little girl who could barely reach

164
00:11:05,519 --> 00:11:06,960
my hip bone when you were a child.

165
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:08,480
Now you are so beautiful.

166
00:11:09,039 --> 00:11:10,480
So pretty.

167
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:11,279
So pretty.

168
00:11:11,399 --> 00:11:12,240
So pretty.

169
00:11:12,639 --> 00:11:13,879
You should show it to Yunfei.

170
00:11:15,039 --> 00:11:15,519
Xiaofei.

171
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:16,840
Look who's here.

172
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,240
Bro.

173
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:22,399
I missed you so much.

174
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:24,000
Oh my god.

175
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:25,399
You look so handsome now.

176
00:11:25,559 --> 00:11:27,080
Look at your hairstyle, your suit,

177
00:11:27,159 --> 00:11:27,799
and your muscles.

178
00:11:27,919 --> 00:11:29,399
Oh my god. You've been working out.

179
00:11:29,600 --> 00:11:31,679
I'm in love with you, bro.

180
00:11:33,799 --> 00:11:35,759
What's wrong? You're not happy to see me?

181
00:11:35,919 --> 00:11:37,120
Why don't you want to see me?

182
00:11:37,279 --> 00:11:38,759
What do you mean?

183
00:11:38,919 --> 00:11:40,320
Brother
